sentence: Wall Street's main indexes slipped on Tuesday following a three-day rally as a drop in Apple shares overshadowed optimism from remarks made by U.S. and China officials in pledging firm commitment to a Phase One trade deal.
ET, the Dow Jones Industrial Average .DJI was down 0.19% at 28,255.48.
The S&P 500 .SPX was up 0.04% at 3,432.57 and the Nasdaq Composite .IXIC was down 0.03% at 11,375.957.
